{"sectionId":754,"sectionIdLiteral":"754","humanId":"lesson-331","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"There is no conflict, for my will is Yours.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 331"},"annotation":"W-331","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-331\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"754#1\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>How foolish, Father, to believe Your Son could cause himself to suffer!</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Could he make a plan for his damnation, and be left without a certain way to his release?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>You love me, Father.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>You could never leave me desolate, to die within a world of pain and cruelty.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>How could I think that Love has left Itself?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>There is no will except the Will of Love.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#1:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>Fear is a dream, and has no will that can conflict with Yours.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#1:8\"><span class=\"snr\">8</span>Conflict is sleep, and peace awakening.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#1:9\"><span class=\"snr\">9</span>Death is illusion; life, eternal truth.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#1:10\"><span class=\"snr\">10</span>There is no opposition to Your Will.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#1:11\"><span class=\"snr\">11</span>There is no conflict, for my will is Yours.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"754#2\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Forgiveness shows us that God‚Äôs Will is One, and that we share it.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Let us look upon the holy sights forgiveness shows today, that we may find the peace of God.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"754#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Amen.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"How foolish, Father, to believe Your Son could cause himself to suffer! Could he make a plan for his damnation, and be left without a certain way to his release? You love me, Father. You could never","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 331: There is no conflict, for my will‚Ä¶ | ACIM","seoDescription":"‚ú® A Course in Miracles with üéß Audio! Read and listen to Lesson¬†331 ‚ÄúThere is no conflict, for my will is Yours‚Äù: How foolish, Father, to believe Your Son could cause himself to suffer!‚Ä¶","desktopBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"12. What Is the Ego?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":753,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-the-ego"]}},{"label":"Lesson 331","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":754,"slugs":["lesson-331","there-is-no-conflict-for-my-will-is-yours"]}}],"mobileBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"12. What Is the Ego?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":753,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-the-ego"]}},{"label":"Lesson 331","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":754,"slugs":["lesson-331","there-is-no-conflict-for-my-will-is-yours"]}}],"seoBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"A Course in Miracles","leadsTo":"dashboard"},{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs